<section class="section" style="padding-top:10px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="prose prose--wide">
      <h3>Independent and broker-owned</h3>
      <p>Everlane isn&rsquo;t a franchise office or a name rented from a national chain &mdash; it&rsquo;s an independent brokerage, owned and run by Serge Osaulenko, a Florida licensed broker, since 2020 (licensed since 2017). When you work with Everlane, the broker you talk to is the one who owns the brokerage.</p>

      <h3>Built around the contract</h3>
      <p>Before real estate, Serge studied it &mdash; degrees in Real Estate and Finance from Florida State &mdash; and then spent fourteen years building and selling a restaurant business. That&rsquo;s where he learned what a contract really is: the quiet place a deal succeeds or falls apart. Reading them closely is still his favorite part of the job, and it&rsquo;s the habit the whole brokerage is organized around &mdash; catch the problem on the page before it becomes a problem at the closing table.</p>

      <h3>A local-market knowledge base, kept current</h3>
      <p>Everlane treats local knowledge as something you build and maintain, not something you claim. The guides and neighborhood chapters on this site are the public face of a knowledge base the brokerage keeps researching and updating as St. Petersburg changes &mdash; flood zones and insurance, neighborhood by neighborhood, the rules that actually govern a short-term rental or a renovation in a historic district. When a client asks a real question, the answer comes from that research. When the answer isn&rsquo;t there yet, it gets added. The point is to be genuinely knowledgeable about this market, in writing, on the record.</p>

      <h3>Honest data, a real person</h3>
      <p>The brokerage built a system to keep this site&rsquo;s market numbers honest: it pulls live MLS data, recomputes the figures, and rebuilds the pages on its own &mdash; and when a number isn&rsquo;t solid, it shows nothing rather than a guess. (Those live numbers switch on when the MLS feed connects; until then the site would rather show you an honest blank than a placeholder.) The guides and neighborhood chapters are researched and drafted with that same studio toolkit, then reviewed, edited, and approved by Serge before anything publishes &mdash; every judgment call, and every published word, is his to own. The machinery keeps the facts current; it doesn&rsquo;t replace the broker. <a href="/ai/">See how the site runs itself &rarr;</a></p>

      <h3>Where Everlane works</h3>
      <p>Serge works where he lives &mdash; from the Pink Streets at Pinellas Point north through St. Petersburg and up the coast toward Clearwater &mdash; and works in English and Russian. Bring him the messy version of your situation; making it clear is the job.</p>
    </div>

